                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.00/4193b: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Commission to Negotiate Peace</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-03-31T17:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 31, 1919, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1393. Referring Department’s telegram March 29 concerning repatriation
                    Czecho-Slovak forces in Siberia, the Secretary of War asks me to say that he
                    feels some definite action is extremely important.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_PW1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
